<h2>Create New Pseudonym</h2>

<p>You can have an unlimited number of pseudonyms attached to your account. This makes it easy to associate any of your content with the appropriate 
pseudonym. For example, if you upload a track under a pseudonym, your track's info will display the pseudonym instead of your real name, however, the 
link will always point back to your account. This makes it easier for people to find your stuff all in one place. This also makes it so you don't have 
to create a new account for each different pseudonym (unless you really, positively, absolutely want to).</p><br>

<%= form_for(@pseudonym) do |f| %>
  <% if @pseudonym.errors.any? %>
    <div id="error_explanation">
      <h2><%= pluralize(@pseudonym.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this pseudonym from being saved:</h2>

      <ul>
      <% @pseudonym.errors.full_messages.each do |message| %>
        <li><%= message %></li>
      <% end %>
      </ul>
    </div>
  <% end %>
  
	<div class="field">
    <div class="tooltip" style="float:right">more info
      <span class="tooltiptext">Pseudonyms added here will be available to you when you go to add new tracks, listings, topics, and blogs.</span>
    </div>
    <%= f.label "Pseudonym", class: "title" %><br />
    <%= f.text_field :name, :autofocus => true, required: true %>
  </div>

  <div class="actions">
    <%= f.submit "Submit", class: "button button_highlight button_block" %>
  </div>
<% end %>

<%= link_to 'Cancel', 'javascript:history.back()' %><br />